article.description: — Jeremiah Kendall had 20 points and Alcorn State beat Mississippi Valley State 72-55 on Monday night, handing the Delta Devils their 26th straight loss dating to last season.
article.headline: Mississippi Valley State skid hits 26 after 72-55 loss to Alcorn State
article.linkText: Mississippi Valley State skid hits 26 after 72-55 loss to Alcorn State
article.story: ITTA BENA, Miss. -- — Jeremiah Kendall had 20 points and Alcorn State beat Mississippi Valley State 72-55 on Monday night, handing the Delta Devils their 26th straight loss dating to last season. Kendall had five rebounds for the Braves (7-17, 6-5 Southwestern Athletic Conference). Jeremiah Gambrell made three 3-pointers and scored 15. Dekedran Thorn had 11 points and also made three 3s. Rayquan Brown led the Delta Devils (0-24, 0-11) with 26 points. Danny Washington added 12 points and five assists. ------ The Associated Press created this story using technology provided by Data Skrive and data from Sportradar.
